8da8			; https://tutorials.eeems.ca/ASMin28Days/lesson/day16.html#cmp 
8da8			 
8da8			; String Length 
8da8			;With a length-prefixed string, finding the length is trivial. For a null-terminated string, the process is decidedly more involved. This is where CPIR comes in. 
8da8			 
8da8			; Get the length of the null-terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
8da8			;    LD     HL, $8000 
8da8			 
8da8			strlenz: 
8da8			 
8da8 af			    XOR    A               ; Zero is the value we are looking for. 
8da9 47			    LD     B, A             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
8daa 4f			    LD     C, A             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
8dab			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
8dab ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
8dad			 
8dad			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
8dad 67			    LD     H, A             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
8dae 6f			    LD     L, A             ; number of bytes 
8daf ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
8db1 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
8db2 c9				ret 
8db3			 
8db3			; Get the length of the A terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
8db3			;    LD     HL, $8000 
8db3			 
8db3			strlent: 
8db3			 
8db3			                  ; A is the value we are looking for. 
8db3 06 00		    LD     B, 0             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
8db5 0e 00		    LD     C, 0             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
8db7			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
8db7 ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
8db9			 
8db9			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
8db9 26 00		    LD     H, 0             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
8dbb 2e 00		    LD     L, 0             ; number of bytes 
8dbd ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
8dbf 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
8dc0 c9				ret 
